{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc3bd4870-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4108"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4108"},"text":"§ 4108.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cooperation and coordination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc3bd4871-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4108/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In carrying out the Secretary’s responsibilities under this chapter, the Secretary shall from time to time consult with the Secretary of Veterans Affairs and keep the Secretary of Veterans Affairs fully advised of activities carried out and all data gathered pursuant to this chapter to insure maximum cooperation and coordination between the Department of Labor and the Department of Veterans Affairs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc3bd4872-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s4108/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Veterans Affairs shall provide to appropriate employment service offices and Department of Labor offices, as designated by the Secretary, on a monthly or more frequent basis, the name and address of each employer located in the areas served by such offices that offer a program of job training which has been approved by the Secretary of Veterans Affairs under section 7 of the Veterans’ Job Training Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s1721"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 1721","children":[],"tail":" note)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc3bd4873-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/540/tV/s502/a"},"text":"P